law.text:
A security interest arising under § 2-401, § 2-505, § 2-711(3), or § 2A-508(5) of this article is subject to this title. However, until the debtor obtains possession of the goods:
The security interest is enforceable, even if § 9-203(b)(3) has not been satisfied;
Filing is not required to perfect the security interest;
The rights of the secured party after default by the debtor are governed by Title 2 or 2A of this article; and
The security interest has priority over a conflicting security interest created by the debtor.
